=== summary ===
It is reasonable to interpret Kant as claiming that _a priori_ knowledge is 
knowledge justified without the aid of experience; and that the two criteria of
such knowledge are necessity and certain universality.

Furthermore a priori knowledge may be distinguished as a analytic




