=== chapter 2 ===
antinomies of pure reason
The underlying issue concerns infinity and infinite series:
 * There is no proof of maximal length but each proof is finitely long.
 * There is no ultimate cause but each sequence of causes is finitely long.
   (This is the weakest statement of the problem.)
 * The set of all things that can be reached in a finite number of steps from a
   given starting point may be infinitely large.

